Pre-Game Insights: Hugo Broos said Morocco were at the World Cup (they made the semifinals of Qatar 2022) but I think they (still) want to win the AFCON, maybe for the last time this will be a chance (for these players) to achieve the highest level.
They were not really very good in the group stages (Morocco drew with the DR Congo but also beat Tanzania and Zambia), but this is still a good team, and it will be a tough battle (on Tuesday).
Hugo Broos said that Bafana can beat them, that is the most important thing we learned.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Bafana Bafana and Morocco meet in the Round of 16 at the ongoing Africa Cup of Nations tournament in Ivory Coast!
Bafana Bafana and Morocco square off in the 2023 Africa Cup of Nations (Afcon) round of 16 at the Stade de San Pédro.
The two sides meet on Tuesday 30 January 2024! Action is scheduled to get underway at 22:00 SAST.
The match between Bafana and Morocco will be televised live on SuperSport PSL as well as SABC1.
Others: Bafana coach Hugo Broos said as quoted by Citizen.
